    <div class="page-break"></div>

    <!-- Overview & Deliverables -->
    <h1>1. Project Overview & Implemented Deliverables</h1>
    <p><strong>GlimSync</strong> is a cutting-edge, AI-powered platform designed for photographers and event organizers to effortlessly manage event media, auto-tag guests using facial recognition, and automatically generate smart captions and tags for photos using advanced AI models.</p>
    
    <h2>✨ Implemented Deliverables Log</h2>
    <p>The following features and visual fixes have been fully implemented and verified in the current production release:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Branding Color Split:</strong> The navbar logo text has been customized to split <code>GlimSync</code> into <strong>Glim</strong> (styled in dark navy blue: <code>#1e3a8a</code>) and <strong>Sync</strong> (styled in solid black: <code>#000000</code>).</li>
        <li><strong>Header Session Layout Fix:</strong> Corrected session logic so that redundant login/register buttons are hidden when a user session is active, showing only the authenticated user profile badge.</li>
        <li><strong>4-Column Feed Layout:</strong> Optimized gallery feeds (Gallery Feed, Downloads, Tagged, and Favorites) to output exactly 4 columns in a row starting at viewport widths of <code>768px</code>/<code>800px</code>, preventing 3-column fallback due to high-DPI Windows display scaling.</li>
        <li><strong>Zoomed Out Aesthetic:</strong> Shrunk gallery card image height from <code>280px</code> to <code>200px</code>/<code>210px</code> for a unified, zoomed-out visual feed structure.</li>
        <li><strong>Star Icon Repositioning:</strong> Moved the favorite star icon to the bottom actions bar on gallery cards, next to likes and comments.</li>
        <li><strong>Folder/Event Management Controls:</strong> Added download and delete capabilities for events and subfolders, restricting deletion access strictly to the uploader.</li>
        <li><strong>Watermarking System:</strong> Implemented robust SVG watermarking utilizing system-compatible Arial fonts and simple vector rectangle backgrounds to ensure reliable background image composite rendering on Vercel instances.</li>
        <li><strong>Admin dashboard Integration:</strong> Configured admin routes (<code>/admin</code>) and seeded a default system admin account (<code>admin@glimsync.com</code> / <code>adminpassword123</code>).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>🛠️ Tech Stack</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Next.js 14, React 19, Tailwind CSS (Vanilla CSS structure), Lucide Icons</li>
        <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Next.js App Router (API Routes)</li>
        <li><strong>Database:</strong> MySQL, Prisma ORM</li>
        <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> NextAuth.js (Credentials/Session based)</li>
        <li><strong>AI & ML:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><code>@vladmandic/face-api</code> (Client-side Facial Recognition)</li>
                <li><code>@google/generative-ai</code> (Gemini Pro Vision for image analysis)</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Cloudinary</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="page-break"></div>

    <!-- Architecture -->
    <h1>2. System Architecture & Flow</h1>
    <p>Below is the system flow architecture describing client interactions with authentication, database models, Cloudinary storage, and AI processing nodes:</p>
    
    <pre>
+-------------------------------------------------------------+
|                     Client (Next.js/React)                  |
+-------------------------------------------------------------+
       |                  |                    |
       | (Session Auth)   | (Direct Upload)    | (Face Detection)
       v                  v                    v
+--------------+   +--------------+   +-----------------------+
|  NextAuth    |   |  Cloudinary  |   | face-api.js (Client)  |
+--------------+   +--------------+   +-----------------------+
       |                  |                    |
       |                  |                    | (Embeddings)
       v                  v                    v
+-------------------------------------------------------------+
|                 Prisma ORM & MySQL Database                 |
+-------------------------------------------------------------+
                               ^
                               | (Smart Captions & Tags)
                        +--------------+
                        | Google Gemini|
                        +--------------+
    </pre>

    <h3>Core Layer Descriptions</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Client Layer:</strong> Runs face detection locally on the client's browser, fetching facial markers using <code>face-api.js</code>. This minimizes server latency and computes face signatures client-side.</li>
        <li><strong>Storage Layer:</strong> Cloudinary manages real-time optimization, image hosting, and fast content delivery (CDN).</li>
        <li><strong>AI Layer:</strong> The backend queries the Google Gemini Vision model asynchronously on upload to auto-generate context-aware tags and descriptions.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="page-break"></div>

    <!-- Database Schema -->
    <h1>3. Database Schema & Relationships</h1>
    <p>The database layer uses Prisma ORM on a MySQL instance. The primary data models are outlined below:</p>

    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Entity</th>
                <th>Description</th>
                <th>Key Relationships</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>User</strong></td>
                <td>Stores user info, role (ADMIN, PHOTOGRAPHER, VIEWER), and biometric face encoding strings.</td>
                <td>One-to-many with Event, Media, Comment, Like, Favorite, UserTag.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Event</strong></td>
                <td>Organizes groups of photos under a specific date/privacy setting.</td>
                <td>One-to-many with Folders and Media files.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Media</strong></td>
                <td>Represents uploaded files, storing CDN links and AI-generated captions.</td>
                <td>Belongs to Event, Folder, and User. Many-to-many with Tags.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Comment / Like</strong></td>
                <td>Tracks standard community reactions on individual photos.</td>
                <td>Linked directly to User and Media models.</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="page-break"></div>

    <!-- Setup Guide -->
    <h1>4. Local Setup & Configuration Guide</h1>
    
    <h2>💻 Installation</h2>
    <p>Follow these steps to run the application locally on your developer machine:</p>
    
    <pre>
# 1. Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/chanchal624/event-management-Glimsync-CIG.git
cd event-management-Glimsync-CIG

# 2. Install package dependencies
npm install
    </pre>

    <h2>⚙️ Environment Configurations (.env)</h2>
    <p>Create a <code>.env</code> file in the project's root folder and populate the following keys:</p>
    <pre>
DATABASE_URL="mysql://username:password@localhost:3306/glimsync_db"
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-32-character-secret"
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME="your_cloudinary_cloud_name"
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY="your_cloudinary_api_key"
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET="your_cloudinary_api_secret"
GEMINI_API_KEY="your_google_gemini_api_key"
    </pre>

    <h2>🚀 Running Database Migrations & Server</h2>
    <pre>
# Generate prisma client and push schema structure to database
npx prisma generate
npx prisma db push

# Start the dev server
npm run dev
    </pre>
    <p>Your local app is now running at: <strong>http://localhost:3000</strong></p>

</div>
